                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 823.00/169.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">McMillin</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 19, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Supreme and superior courts united with army, navy, Archbishop of Lima and many
                    business firms make official calls on Benavides today. Strong French banks
                    telegraph support. Congress expected to meet again this week to confirm Friday’s
                    action.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">McMillin</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
